review_blob: It looked pretty, but when I tasted it I wondered if I'd be up all night from the caffeine.  They weren't kidding about the "java" part.  It tasted of coffee from start to finish, with a hint afterward of that soapiness that I normally associate with porters.  Pretty good stuff, but I've had better stouts.

Dark brown color, cloudy but not opaque.  Not much of a head, thin and watery compared to most other dark beers I've had.  I couldn't identify and particular strains of taste other than what I would characterize as plain dark beerness.  Not anything special, but WAY better than anything else commonly available for $6 per 12-pack.

Dark brown with a hint of red, with a medium-sized off-white head.  Slides over the tongue like syrup and leaves a noticeable residue on the roof of my mouth.  The initial taste is is cinnamon but gives way to smoke and a couple other things I can't identify.  Between the obnoxious residue on the roof of my mouth and the curiousity about those flavors, I keep taking another drink, but I'm not convinced this is one of my favorites.

Reddish brown color.  Palate smooth and rather thin.  Taste bitter throughout (surprise!) with a little something I couldn't place in the finish.  It seemed vaguely soapy or leathery, and most closely resembled the smell of a room in barn full of saddles and other equestrian equipment.  Better than average but not something I'd go out of my way to get.
